cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.SP, cs.MM, cs.NA. 

The paper deals with robust compressive sensing reconstruction, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), signal processing (cs.SP), mathematical modeling (cs.MM), and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper proposes an adaptive filtering based robust CS reconstruction algorithm, which combines the maximum correntropy criterion (MCC) with $l_0$ regularization. Therefore, the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CV (computer vision) and cs.SI (social and information networks).
